# Quantumult X - Apple Push Notification Service / APNs
# Purpose: route APNs through proxy to improve notification delivery for
# overseas apps such as Telegram and X / Twitter on China-region networks.
# Apple documents APNs device connections on TCP 5223, with TCP 443 fallback,
# and recommends allowing 17.0.0.0/8 or the narrower ranges below.

# --- APNs domains ---
HOST-SUFFIX,push.apple.com,proxy
HOST-SUFFIX,push-apple.com.akadns.net,proxy
HOST-KEYWORD,apple.com.edgekey.net,proxy

# Provider API endpoints are included for completeness. They are mainly used by
# app servers, but matching them is harmless in client-side proxy profiles.
HOST,api.push.apple.com,proxy
HOST,api.sandbox.push.apple.com,proxy

# --- APNs IPv4 ranges published by Apple ---
IP-CIDR,17.249.0.0/16,proxy,no-resolve
IP-CIDR,17.252.0.0/16,proxy,no-resolve
IP-CIDR,17.57.144.0/22,proxy,no-resolve
IP-CIDR,17.188.128.0/18,proxy,no-resolve
IP-CIDR,17.188.20.0/23,proxy,no-resolve

# --- APNs IPv6 ranges published by Apple ---
IP-CIDR6,2620:149:a44::/48,proxy,no-resolve
IP-CIDR6,2403:300:a42::/48,proxy,no-resolve
IP-CIDR6,2403:300:a51::/48,proxy,no-resolve
IP-CIDR6,2a01:b740:a42::/48,proxy,no-resolve
